OL,6,FShe said: "It's part of living history
OL,7,Fwhen you come here to get married on
OL,8,Fyour wedding day.
OL,10,F"It's tradition, people have heard of
OL,11,Fit, the romance and in days gone by of
OL,12,Fcourse.J"it was the place for
OL,13,Frebellious love as they tired to run
OL,14,Facross the border to be married
OL,15,Fwithout consent from parents, because
OL,16,Fof the age difference, between England
OL,17,Fand Scotland.
OL,19,F"It's the atmosphere, the love, you
OL,20,Fcan't really explain it.
